# OSPF Explanation

OSPF (Open Shortest Path First) is used as the routing protocol.

- Process ID: 10
- Area: 0 (Backbone)

## Why OSPF?
- Fast convergence
- Scalable
- Industry standard

## How it works:
- Routers share routes with neighbors
- Each router builds a routing table
- Best path selected using cost

## Networks Advertised:
- Router interconnections (10.10.10.x)
- All VLAN networks (192.168.x.x)
